about.description:
Google Cloud Memorystore for Redis API is a Google Cloud service that lets client applications communicate with a fully managed Redis service for Google Cloud. Applications running on Google Cloud can achieve extreme performance by leveraging the highly scalable, available, secure Redis service without the burden of managing complex Redis deployments.
See the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/redis/latest/index.html#quick-start).
about.summary: Google Cloud Redis API client library

name: google-cloud-redis
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "google-cloud-redis" %}
{% set version = "2.15.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/google-cloud-redis-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: baaf93114e4acb752e6a06b5f58e7c50bf683eb0e138645fece76e0a0159c188

build:
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 0

requirements:
  host:
    - python >=3.7
    - pip
  run:
    - python >=3.7
    - google-api-core >=1.34.1,<3.0.0dev,!=2.0.*,!=2.1.*,!=2.2.*,!=2.3.*,!=2.4.*,!=2.5.*,!=2.6.*,!=2.7.*,!=2.8.*,!=2.9.*,!=2.10.*
    - google-api-core-grpc
    - google-auth >=2.14.1,<3.0.0dev
    - proto-plus >=1.22.3,<2.0.0dev
    - protobuf >=3.19.5,<5.0.0dev,!=3.20.0,!=3.20.1,!=4.21.0,!=4.21.1,!=4.21.2,!=4.21.3,!=4.21.4,!=4.21.5

test:
  imports:
    - grpc
    - google.cloud.redis
    - google.cloud.redis_v1
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-python/tree/main/packages/google-cloud-redis
  summary: Google Cloud Redis API client library
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_family: Apache
  license_file: LICENSE
  description: "Google Cloud Memorystore for Redis API is a Google Cloud service that lets client applications communicate with a fully managed Redis service for Google Cloud. Applications running on Google Cloud can achieve extreme performance by leveraging the highly scalable, available, secure Redis service without the
    burden of managing complex Redis deployments.\nSee the [quick start guide](https://googleapis.dev/python/redis/latest/index.html#quick-start)."

  doc_url: https://googleapis.dev/python/redis/latest/index.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/googleapis/python-redis

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - parthea
    - xylar
